Soccer No.1, says Becks | Beijing 2008 | Sports | The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata)
                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Soccer No.1, says Becks
                      
	Soccer will always be the worlds No.1 sport, Englands David Beckham said at the Beijing Olympics. Obviously for me, its the best sport in the world, so I think it should always be on the top of the list, Beckham said on a visit for the closing of the Games on Sunday. Meanwhile, an Indian-origin schoolgirl, Tayyiba Dudhwala from east London starred alongside Beckham at the closing ceremony of Beijing Olympics on Sunday.               
	A record 4.4 billion people watched the Olympic Games from August 8 to 17, making it the most watched in history, a top market research firm said on Sunday. The Nielsen company drew television audience data from 38 nations and regions, including host China, the US, Brazil, South Africa, Italy and Australia.               
	Worlds fastest man and the cynosure of Beijing Olympics, Usain Bolt has won the hearts and minds of Chinese people, this time off the track, when he made a personal donation of $50,000 for children of the earthquake-hit Sichuan province.                                                                                                                          
